20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-10-1120 of Title 27A, unless
23 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 16837 Page 1

1 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma
2 Biosolids Land Application Research Pilot Program Act".
3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-10-1121 of Title 27A, unless
5 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. There is hereby created at Oklahoma State University (OSU)
7 the Oklahoma Biosolids Land Application Research "Pilot Program".
8 The Pilot Program shall be administered by the Department of
9 Environmental Quality (DEQ) in cooperation with the Division of
10 Agricultural Sciences and Natural Resources in coordination with the
11 OSU College of Engineering, Architecture and Technology, the OSU
12 Department of Environmental Science, and the Cooperative Extension
13 Service. The Pilot Program shall operate for an initial five-year
14 period.
15 B. The Pilot Program shall:
16 1. Identify and approve study plots on agricultural lands,
17 including, but not limited to, OSU-owned research farms and, as
18 appropriate, cooperating private farms;
19 2. Develop biosolids application protocols, including:
20 a. nutrient content evaluation,
21 b. pathogen and contaminant screening (including
22 perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS),
23 heavy metals, and pharmaceuticals),
24 c. application rates, and
Req. No. 16837 Page 2

1 d. soil amendment practices;
2 3. Conduct agronomic research, including crop yield impacts,
3 soil health changes, and nutrient cycling;
4 4. Conduct environmental impact studies, including:
5 a. surface and groundwater monitoring,
6 b. soil residual testing, and
7 c. air quality, odor, and vector considerations;
8 5. Assess regulatory models, including best management
9 practices, permitting options, and compliance structures suitable
10 for Oklahoma;
11 6. Coordinate with the DEQ and may utilize biosolids supplied
12 by Oklahoma municipal wastewater treatment facilities that meet DEQ
13 and Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) standards; and
14 7. Provide outreach and education to Oklahoma farmers,
15 ranchers, conservation districts, and municipalities through OSU
16 Extension programs.
17 C. A report shall be submitted annually to the Governor, the
18 President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate, the Speaker of
19 the Oklahoma House of Representatives, and the DEQ regarding
20 findings, data, and recommendations. Annual reports shall be
21 submitted no later than December 1st and include:
22 1. Agronomic outcomes;
23 2. Environmental monitoring results;
24 3. Risk assessments;
Req. No. 16837 Page 3

1 4. Recommendations for statewide standards or rules; and
2 5. Cost-benefit analysis for farmers and municipalities.
3 D. OSU may partner with private agricultural landowners who
4 volunteer to participate in research trials. OSU shall secure
5 written consent, ensure DEQ compliance, and provide guidelines for
6 application, monitoring, and sampling. No landowner shall be held
7 liable for environmental impacts resulting solely from adherence to
8 OSU protocols developed under the Pilot Program.
9 E. Biosolids applied under the Pilot Program shall be exempt
10 from state permitting otherwise required under environmental or land
11 application rules, only to the extent necessary to conduct
12 controlled research, and only when research protocols meet or exceed
13 DEQ and EPA requirements. OSU shall coordinate with DEQ to ensure
14 proper recordkeeping and transport documentation.
15 F. The Pilot Program may be funded by legislative
16 appropriations, federal research grants, municipal contributions,
17 private or industry research partnerships, or in-kind contributions
18 of biosolids or laboratory services. Funds for administering the
19 Pilot Program shall be deposited into the Oklahoma Biosolids Land
20 Application Research Pilot Program Act Revolving Fund created in
21 Section 3 of this act.
22 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-10-1122 of Title 27A, unless
24 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
Req. No. 16837 Page 4

1 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
2 for the Department of Environmental Quality to be designated the
3 "Oklahoma Biosolids Land Application Research Pilot Program Act
4 Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject
5 to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all monies received
6 by the Department from appropriations, apportionments, donations,
7 and federal grants received for the purpose of conducting the
8 provisions of the Oklahoma Biosolids Land Application Research Pilot
9 Program Act created pursuant to Section 2 of this act. All monies
10 accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby appropriated and may
11 be budgeted and expended by the Department for the purpose provided
12 for in this section. Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon
13 warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
14 prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of Management and
15 Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
16 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
